Defending Kenya Champion Baldev Singh Chager beat title rival Carl “Flash” Tundo on the first stage of KCB Nanyuki Rally to take an 11 seconds lead. Navigated by Ravi Soni in VW Polo R5, Chager cleared the opening 28km in 00:19.45.3minutes ahead of Mitsubishi Evo ace Tundo who clocked 00:19.56.3minutes. Ugandan Amaanraj Rai came third in the first stage clocking 00:20.56minutes. Chager was again 24seconds faster than Tundo in the longest 41.26km Ole Naishu stage where crews endured a long and energy-sapping drive. The rally was flagged off by Deputy Laikipia Governor John Mwaniki at the Greystones ranch which also hosted the Rally HQs, Remote Refuel Zone and Service Park. Also in attendance was KMSF Chairman Phineas Kimathi who lauded Nanyuki Rally Group (NRG) for running a compact private land event. Also Read: A total of 23 drivers started off the event which counts towards the seventh round of the KCB Kenya National Rally Championship (KNRC). The event features a 77.29km three-stage loop at Greystone and Ole Naishu Ranches which is being repeated twice. The KNRC has been to Nakuru, Naivasha for WRC Safari Rally and ARC Equator Rally, Voi, Machakos and Ramisi. The series will culminate with the RSC and Guru Nanak rounds later in the month. RESULTS AFTER CS1 MLIMA (28Km) 1.Baldev Chager (VW Polo R4) 00:19.45.3  Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam